76561198046826025,Recommended,214130,8395885,"Posted: 29 December, 2013",all,waterfish333,"High quality graphics and very smooth keyboard controls make this an excellent flight sim. The detail on the aircraft itself is impressive, ranging from seeing the steering components actually move to minimal, but visible, damage on the airplane. Landing and taking off is simplified.The biggest issue I have with Aerofly is the quality of the environment. Clouds are not highly detailed and the ground is very barren. The occasional cluster of buildings you might fly over (or through), are the ""large cities,"" while the rest of the landscape has nothing besides Google Earth-like textures. The mountains are nicely done though.Overall, if you are looking for an easy to pick up, quick to learn flight sim, it's hard to do better than Aerofly FS, but if you are looking for a serious, challenging, realistic flight simulator, look elsewhere, such as MS flight sim. It will entertain you, but not really challenge you."
